11: Typically de novo genome sequencing projects generate multiple assemblies of the same sample using
12: different softwares and/or different parameters of the same software. Instead of discarding the
13: extra assemblies, Metassembler merges them to the top assembly using mate-pair information and
14: whole-genome alignments, in order to generate a single superior assembly. The final assembly will
15: combine the best locally superior assemblies throughout the genome.
